TopicTitle: [1.12.x] NOT RO - Kerbal Construction Time - Unrapid Planned Assembly

Articles.Content:
14 hours ago, theJesuit said:

Hi everyone!

For the VABandPartCount preset, I'd like to change it to allow for multiple multiple builds at the same time.  Currently it is one after the other after the other.

So for example, on the tier 1 VAB have one after another,

In the tier 2 have two concurrent builds

In the tier 3 have three concurrent builds

 

Ideally, this would keep the same length of time for the builds, speed up for each tier, and based on part count.

 

Could someone please suggest how I would go about this?

 

Thanks!

Peace.

RP-1 already adds extra build queues based on the VAB level: https://github.com/KSP-RO/RP-0/blob/master/GameData/RP-0/KCT_Presets/RP1_KCT_Presets.cfg#L47

[L] is the 0-based level of the VAB and [ I ]  is the 0-based index of the vessel inside the build queue.

Edited September 2, 2019 by siimav

5 hours ago, siimav said:

RP-1 already adds extra build queues based on the VAB level: https://github.com/KSP-RO/RP-0/blob/master/GameData/RP-0/KCT_Presets/RP1_KCT_Presets.cfg#L47

[L] is the 0-based level of the VAB and [ I ]  is the 0-based index of the vessel inside the build queue.

Thanks.  I nutted it out this morning.  The BuildRateFormula = (([L]*[L])+2)/3*sign(2*[L]-+1)

needs to be this.   The stuff in the sign parentheses needs to be this to get 2 build queues in tier 1, 4 in tier 2 and 6 build queues in tier 3.

Don't ask me how it works... it just does Copied out of the default settings and using the wiki as a guide.

When I get time I'll PR LGG''s github to get it added as another option.

Peace.
